issues.suggested_fix:
Extract a shared private helper, e.g. `fn lower_quoted_string_literal(&self, node: tree_sitter::Node, quote: char) -> Option<Expr>`, and have both lower_string_literal and lower_single_quoted_string delegate to it. Example:

    fn lower_quoted_string_literal(&self, node: tree_sitter::Node, quote: char) -> Option<Expr> {
        let text = self.node_text(node);
        // Error recovery: malformed nodes may lack closing quote
        let s = text
            .strip_prefix(quote)
            .and_then(|s| s.strip_suffix(quote))
            .unwrap_or(text)
            .to_string();
        Some(Expr { kind: ExprKind::StringLiteral(s), span: self.span(node) })
    }

    fn lower_string_literal(&self, node: tree_sitter::Node) -> Option<Expr> {
        self.lower_quoted_string_literal(node, '"')
    }

    fn lower_single_quoted_string(&self, node: tree_sitter::Node) -> Option<Expr> {
        self.lower_quoted_string_literal(node, '\'')
    }
